# PixiJS API (authoritative reference)

When working with PixiJS in this project, treat the PixiJS docs (v8) as the source of truth for APIs, class names, option shapes, lifecycle, and best practices.

- Primary index (LLM docs): `https://pixijs.com/llms.txt`
- Prefer deep links under `https://pixijs.com/8.x/` when citing specifics.

## How to use this rule

- If you’re about to use a PixiJS type/class/method (e.g. `Application`, `Assets`, `Ticker`, `Container`, `Sprite`, `Graphics`, `Text`, `RenderLayers`, `RenderGroups`), verify it exists and matches v8 docs before coding.
- Use the docs to confirm **resource lifecycle** and **cleanup** patterns (textures, base textures, GPU resources, caching).
- For performance-sensitive visualizers, consult the docs sections on **performance tips**, **render loop**, **garbage collection**, **culling**, and **cacheAsTexture** before introducing new per-frame allocations.

